\title{Tutorials}{tutorials}

\use-plugin{concourse-docs}

If you're just getting started with Concourse we'd recommend that you start with
the \link{Concourse Tutorials}{https://concoursetutorial.com/} developed and
maintained by our friends at \link{Stark & Wayne}{https://starkandwayne.com/}.

Below you'll also find additional tutorials, guides and articles written by various
members of the Concourse community.

\warn{
  These guides are not written or maintained by the Concourse maintainers. As usual,
  use at your own risk!
}

\section{
  \title{Learning Concourse}

  \link{Concourse Tutorial}{https://concoursetutorial.com/} by \link{Stark & Wayne}{https://starkandwayne.com/}.
  A linear sequence of tutorials for learning how to use Concourse.

  \link{How To Set Up Continuous Integration Pipelines with Concourse CI on Ubuntu 16.04}{https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-set-up-continuous-integration-pipelines-with-concourse-ci-on-ubuntu-16-04} by \link{Digital Ocean}{https://www.digitalocean.com/}

  \link{Concourse Samples}{https://github.com/pivotalservices/concourse-pipeline-samples} by \link{Pivotal Services}{https://github.com/pivotalservices}.
  This repository contains code samples and recipes for common Concourse pipelines and deployment patterns

  \link{Spring Cloud Pipelines}{https://cloud.spring.io/spring-cloud-pipelines/} by \link{Marcin Grzejszczak}{https://spring.io/team/marcingrzejszczak}

  \link{Creating a continuous integration pipeline in Concourse for a test-infused ASP.NET Core app}{https://seroter.wordpress.com/2018/06/06/creating-a-continuous-integration-pipeline-in-concourse-for-a-test-infused-asp-net-core-app/}
  by \ghuser{rseroter}

  \link{Concourse caching for Java Maven and Gradle builds}{http://www.java-allandsundry.com/2017/08/concourse-caching-for-java-maven-and.html} by \ghuser{bijukunjummen}
}

